&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Surgical Skin Specialist Nurse  (Band 6) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Part time – 22.5 hours&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our Dermatology department has an exciting opportunity for a Band 6 Clinical Nurse Specialist to join our well established, friendly and expanding county wide team. We run a phototherapy service, have outpatient clinics at 3 hospital sites, undertake regular minor skin surgery lists and also offer Mohs micrographic surgery at Worcester Royal Hospital. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ideal candidate will be a team player able to support patient pathways in dermatology and will be experienced in skin surgery. You will be an excellent communicator committed to ensuring high quality patient care. If you are motivated and keen to make a difference to people with dermatological conditions and skin cancers we would like to hear from you. In return you will be well supported in this job role and welcomed to the team with exciting opportunities for further personal and professional development.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Contact: Wendy Bramhall Band 7 Skin Oncology CNS 01905 733876 or email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;wbramhall@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; or Charlotte Gray, Dermatology Nurse Consultant via email at &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;charlotte.gray7@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
